# Text Elements
Note: it does not match seperate occurences of r in seperate substrings.
It only reapplies the regularexpression r 1~5 times.

so a*b{1,2}a* accepts aba and abba but not abab. ^CpuhUXiA

The only difference of this from a normal r+ is that it runs a minimum 1 but maximum 5. ^tHY2LCEv

we can extend this indefinitely to get r{1,N}. ^xx1aiqOK

we can skip this step for the nodes that only
traversed r < minimum times. ^1pQZKURU

example: ^gSY5TALk

Finally we can just convert this back to a regular language ^BLukwtD2
